## Phase Status

Phase 1 is done. Phase 2 is done. Phase 3 is done. Phase 4 is done. Phase 5
remains deferred. Phase 6 is done. Phase 7 is done. Phase 8 is done.

The Phase 1 scaffold adds the unified public workspace vocabulary beside the
existing isolated-workspace exports.

The Phase 2 slice makes `sandbox.isolation.enter` and the test compact-remount
path accept caller-facing `workspace_root`, resolves that root to the
LayerStack workspace binding internally, and keeps legacy `layer_stack_root`
accepted through explicit compatibility adapters. It does not implement the
future create/run/capture/destroy lifecycle APIs.

Phase 2 adversarial review follow-up tightened the root-resolution contract:
discovered bindings must live at their declared `layer_stack_root`, cached
runtime state now tracks `workspace_root` as part of its binding identity,
stateful resolution no longer bypasses ambiguity checks, malformed dual-root
payloads cannot silently fall back to legacy `layer_stack_root`, and
test-remount invalid root requests preserve `invalid_argument` error shaping.

The Phase 3 slice moves Host command workspace lifecycle ownership out of
hidden command start behavior and into `WorkspaceRuntime`. Host command routes
now ask the runtime to resolve the legacy `layer_stack_root` compatibility
binding, acquire the bounded base lease, create the `HostWorkspace`, and
then hand a command context to `CommandOps`. `CommandOps` still owns process
spawning, wait/progress/stdin/cancel mechanics, registry state, transcripts,
capture, and finalization.

The Phase 4 slice makes `WorkspaceRuntime` the command/file route authority.
Runtime route contexts now decide active isolated handle vs Host/direct
fallback and return stable route trace facts to adapters. Command adapters parse
wire args, record returned route metadata, and invoke `CommandOps` with the
returned execution target while the runtime-owned mode gate remains held during
command start. File adapters parse wire args, record returned route metadata,
invoke the selected direct or isolated backend, and ask the runtime to complete
isolated liveness touches after successful isolated file operations.

The Phase 6 slice moves workspace crate code into the responsibility-based
folder structure without changing behavior. Shared overlay primitives now live
under `overlay/`; isolated-network workspace create/destroy/recovery/lease helpers live
under `lifecycle/`; remount state, report/plan, and apply logic live under
`lifecycle/remount/`; holder control, setns-runner prep, FD mapping, and cgroup
creation live under `namespace/`; Host and isolated mode exports route through
thin `network_mode/` adapters; and veth/IP-pool, DNS, rtnetlink, and netfilter
dedicated-network setup/cleanup internals live under `isolated_setup/`.
Legacy root `capture`, `dirs`, and `tree` modules were thin public re-export
shims during Phase 6, while unused internal isolated-workspace namespace/network
shims were removed. No Phase 5 capture behavior, Phase 7 holder/setns-only
execution changes, Host holder-backed namespace creation, Phase 8 legacy export
retirement, publish behavior change, packaging, live E2E, or `ops.json`
regeneration was implemented in the Phase 6 slice.

The Phase 7 slice removes workspace command dependence on fresh namespace
initialization. Host command workspace creation now launches `ns-holder` with
`NamespaceNetwork::Host`, opens user/mount/PID namespace FDs, mounts the
overlay through the setns helper, and carries private holder cleanup in the
Host workspace value. Isolated-network workspace creation now passes
`NamespaceNetwork::Isolated` explicitly, preserving the dedicated network
namespace plus existing veth, DNS, and netfilter setup. Workspace command
preparation now always serializes `RunMode::SetNs`; missing holder namespace
FDs fail as command preparation errors instead of falling back to `FreshNs`.
`FreshNs` was preserved only for legacy/non-workspace subprocess
compatibility. No Phase 8 legacy export/name retirement, publish behavior
change, capture behavior change, packaging, live E2E, or `ops.json`
regeneration was implemented.

The Phase 8 slice retires the legacy workspace source paths and root exports.
Host implementation types moved into `network_mode/host.rs`. Isolated
handle/manager/error/caps/context implementation types moved into
`network_mode/isolated.rs`. The workspace crate root no longer exports
`HostWorkspace`, `HostWorkspaceError`, `overlay_run_dirs`, the legacy
isolated `WorkspaceHandle`, `WorkspaceModeManager`, `WorkspaceModeContext`, or
`WorkspaceModeHandle`; `workspace::WorkspaceHandle` is now the unified
public DTO. Daemon runtime, op adapters, and operation command/file code import
concrete implementation types through scoped mode paths and overlay helpers
through `workspace::overlay`. The legacy root `capture.rs`, `dirs.rs`, and
`tree.rs` paths were removed. Wire compatibility remains only where current
operation contracts require it, including legacy `layer_stack_root` inputs;
route and response literals now use `host` and `isolated`. No publish
behavior, capture behavior, `FreshNs` compatibility, holder/setns execution
semantics, packaging, live E2E, or `ops.json` regeneration was changed.

